                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-229-off1319 t18200412-229-crimeloc1321"></join>. On the 12th of April, between nine and ten o'clock in the evening, I stood on the opposite side of the way, the prisoner and another came to the window and took the bason and ewer; I pursued and took him. He said,</p>
               <p>"Have pity, for I am in distress."</p>
               <p>
            
